# Cursor MCP Configuration for RunHub Directory

## Supabase Database Access
This project uses Supabase as the database. Please use the Supabase MCP to examine database structure and data.

Key tables:
- `run_clubs` - Main table containing running club information
- `webflow_import` - Import table for migrated data

Important columns in `run_clubs`:
- `run_details` - Array of text descriptions for up to 7 runs (legacy format)
- `run_sessions` - Array of JSONB objects with structured run data (new format)
- `run_days` - Array of days when club meets
- `status` - Club approval status ('pending', 'approved', 'rejected')

## Current Task
We're working on parsing existing `run_details` text arrays into structured `run_sessions` JSONB arrays to improve data flexibility and display options. 